problem:
The orthocenter of triangle $ABC$ divides altitude $\overline{CF}$ into segments with lengths $HF = 6$ and $HC = 15.$  Calculate $\tan A \tan B.$

[asy]
unitsize (1 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E, F, H;

A = (0,0);
B = (5,0);
C = (4,4);
D = (A + reflect(B,C)*(A))/2;
E = (B + reflect(C,A)*(B))/2;
F = (C + reflect(A,B)*(C))/2;
H = extension(A,D,B,E);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(C--F);

label("$A$", A, SW);
label("$B$", B, SE);
label("$C$", C, N);
label("$F$", F, S);
dot("$H$", H, W);
[/asy]

solution:
Draw altitudes $\overline{BE}$ and $\overline{CF}.$

[asy]
unitsize (1 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E, F, H;

A = (0,0);
